{"word":"μεταιτέω","slug":"μεταιτέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μεταιτέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to demand one's share of</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>: also <el>μεταιτεῖν μέρος τινός</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>μ. παρά τινος</el> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to beg of, ask alms of</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>to beg, solicit</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}